name: Lemon-Oregano Chicken Kebabs with Cucumber-Tomato Salad and Cauli Rice
description: Bright, herb-lemon chicken kebabs served with a crisp cucumber-tomato salad and quick sautéed cauliflower rice. Mild, fast, and keto-friendly for a family dinner.
prep_steps: If using oven, set broiler to high; otherwise place a grill pan on the stove (do not heat yet).
Zest and juice the lemon; keep separate.
cook_steps: Season the chicken kebabs with half the lemon zest, half the lemon juice, minced garlic, 1.5 tbsp olive oil, 1 tsp oregano, salt, and black pepper; toss to coat.
Stovetop option: Heat a grill pan over medium-high. Cook kebabs 3–4 minutes per side until cooked through (165°F/74°C).
Oven option: Place kebabs on a foil-lined tray and broil 6–8 minutes, turning once, until cooked through.

While kebabs cook, make salad: In a bowl combine cucumber, cherry tomatoes, red onion, remaining lemon zest and juice, 1 tbsp olive oil, a pinch of oregano, salt, black pepper, and most of the parsley; toss.
Heat a large skillet over medium with 1 tbsp olive oil. Add cauliflower rice, season with salt and black pepper, and sauté 3–5 minutes until hot and tender-crisp.
Plate cauliflower rice, top with kebabs, and serve salad on the side. Finish with remaining parsley.
